 Type Intent Optional Attributes Name integer(kind=c_int), value :: n1 The first node index. integer(kind=c_int), value :: n2 The second node index. Return Value integer Description Look up the edge index between a node and its neighbor. The Fortran 1-first convention should be used when providing\narguments. Conversion to C's convention is done under-the-hood. Warning If nothing is found, 0 is returned.","tags":"","url":"interface/get_edge_no.html"},{"title":"create_adj_list – DGSWEM Documentation","text":"interface public  subroutine create_adj_list(np, nedges, nedno1, nedno2) bind(C, name='create_adj_list') Arguments Type Intent Optional Attributes Name integer(kind=c_int), value :: np Number of nodes in the mesh. integer(kind=c_int), value :: nedges Number of edges in the mesh. integer(kind=c_int) :: nedno1 (nedges) List of starting node indexes for each edge. integer(kind=c_int) :: nedno2 (nedges) List of terminal node indexes for each edge. Description Create an adjacency list for each node, i.e. a list of its\nneighbors. The structure is a list of lists of pairs. Each node gets\na list of neighbors. Each neighbor is represented with a pair: the\nadjacent node index and the edge index. Note that these are converted\nto C's 0-first convention under-the-hood.","tags":"","url":"interface/create_adj_list.html"},{"title":"ALLOC_EDGES0 – DGSWEM Documentation","text":"public  subroutine ALLOC_EDGES0() Arguments None","tags":"","url":"proc/alloc_edges0.html"},{"title":"ALLOC_EDGES1 – DGSWEM Documentation","text":"public  subroutine ALLOC_EDGES1() Arguments None","tags":"","url":"proc/alloc_edges1.html"},{"title":"ALLOC_DG1 – DGSWEM Documentation","text":"public  subroutine ALLOC_DG1(MNBFR) Arguments Type Intent Optional Attributes Name integer :: MNBFR","tags":"","url":"proc/alloc_dg1.html"},{"title":"ALLOC_DG2 – DGSWEM Documentation","text":"public  subroutine ALLOC_DG2(MNFFR) Arguments Type Intent Optional Attributes Name integer :: MNFFR","tags":"","url":"proc/allo